external_knowledge:
- The minimum temperature is the lowest temperature recorded; 
- The maximum temperature is the highest temperature recorded; 
- The average temperature is the average of all recorded temperatures, calculated by summing all temperature readings and dividing by the total number of readings; 
- Average humidity is calculated similarly to average temperature, using humidity readings.

sql:
SELECT *
FROM temperature_readings
WHERE temp_c < -50 OR temp_c > 50;

SELECT *
FROM temperature_readings
WHERE (humidity < 0 OR humidity > 100) AND data_validity = 1;

SELECT AVG(temp_f) AS Average_Temperature
FROM temperature_readings
WHERE temp_c < -50 OR temp_c > 50;
